On May 5, 2017, the President signed H.R. 244 into law. This law provides full-year appropriations for fiscal year 2017, which will last until September 30, 2017. The appropriations apply to all agencies, except for those covered by division A of the Continuing Appropriations and Military Construction, Veterans Affairs, and Related Agencies Appropriations Act 2017, and Zika Response and Preparedness Act (Public Law 114-223). Division A specifically provides full-year funding until September 30, 2017, for projects and activities related to military construction, veterans affairs, and related agencies.